Note:
Runa Standard Library: Java Interop Module

This module provides comprehensive Java Virtual Machine (JVM) integration capabilities,
enabling seamless interoperation between Runa and Java/JVM languages. Features JNI
integration, reflection API access, and full JVM lifecycle management.

Key Features:
- JVM initialization and lifecycle management
- JNI (Java Native Interface) integration
- Java reflection API access
- Bidirectional method invocation
- Exception handling across language boundaries
- Garbage collection coordination
- Class loading and bytecode manipulation
- JAR file loading and management
- Thread management and synchronization
- Zero-copy data exchange for primitive arrays
- JavaFX and Swing GUI integration support
- Spring Framework integration capabilities
:End Note

Import "interop/ffi" as FFI
Import "collections/dict" as Dict
Import "collections/list" as List
Import "datetime/time" as Time
Import "../../uuid" as UUID
Import "../../errors" as Errors
Import "../../logging" as Log
Import "../../os" as OS
Import "io/file" as File

Note: JVM Runtime Type System
Type called "JavaRuntime":
    runtime_id as String
    jvm_handle as Integer
    jni_env as Integer
    jvm_version as JavaVersion
    classpath as List[String]
    loaded_jars as Dictionary[String, JarFile]
    loaded_classes as Dictionary[String, JavaClass]
    thread_manager as JavaThreadManager
    gc_coordinator as JavaGCCoordinator
    exception_handler as JavaExceptionHandler
    reflection_cache as JavaReflectionCache
    jni_references as JNIReferenceManager
    performance_monitor as JavaPerformanceMonitor
    security_manager as JavaSecurityManager

